EDITORS' PICKS 
 
Fix Your PC Clock -- Permanently 
  
Every week, your system clock loses a few minutes. These utilities 
correct the problem by synchronizing your PC with an atomic clock.  
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/collection/0,collid,604,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
 
Dimension 4  
Keep your system's clock correct by connecting to an Internet Time 
Server.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,1856,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
AtomTime 
Keep your system's clock on time by connecting it to the atomic clock 
in Boulder, Colorado.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,2448,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
Atomic Clock Sync  
Keep your computer's clock accurate using an atomic clock server.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,16627,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
WebTime  
Synchronize your system's clock with an atomic clock, and avoid losing 
precious fractions of a second.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,7572,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
Rocket.Time  
Keep your computer's time accurate by having it contact an Internet 
Time Server.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,17628,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
YATS32  
Set your time to an Internet time server, or have computers on your 
network set their time to yours.   
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/file_description/0,fid,16733,tk,picks,00.asp 
 
For a full list of this week's Editors' Picks, go to: 
http://www.pcworld.com/downloads/collection/0,collid,604,tk,picks,00.asp                          
           
